OL,4,CApple Daily: HK pro-democracy paper
OL,5,Ccould 'shut within days', says adviser
OL,6, Hong Kong pro-democracy paper Apple
OL,7, Daily could be forced to shut down in a
OL,8, "matter of days", said an adviser of
OL,9, the paper's jailed founder Jimmy Lai.
OL,11,FAuthorities last week froze HK$18m
OL,12,F($2.3m; #1.64m) of assets owned by
OL,13,Fthree companies linked to Apple Daily.
OL,15,FMark Simon told the BBC the paper could
OL,16,F"do nothing while none of its bank
OL,17,Faccounts are functioning".
OL,19,FApple Daily, a well-read tabloid, is
OL,20,Ffrequently critical of Hong Kong and
OL,21,Fmainland Chinese leadership.
